clauses.body_md:
7.1 **Notification**: The Processor shall notify the Controller without undue delay (and in any event within {{breach_notification_hours}} hours) after becoming aware of a Personal Data Breach affecting the Controller's Personal Data.

7.2 **Breach Information**: The notification under Clause 7.1 shall, to the extent possible, include:

   (a) a description of the nature of the Personal Data Breach, including, where possible, the categories and approximate number of Data Subjects concerned and the categories and approximate number of Personal Data records concerned;

   (b) the likely consequences of the Personal Data Breach;

   (c) a description of the measures taken or proposed to be taken by the Processor to address the Personal Data Breach and, where appropriate, to mitigate its possible adverse effects; and

   (d) the name and contact details of the Processor's data protection officer or other contact point from whom more information may be obtained.

7.3 **Investigation and Remediation**: The Processor shall:

   (a) investigate the Personal Data Breach promptly and diligently;

   (b) take reasonable steps to mitigate the effects of the Personal Data Breach and to prevent further breaches;

   (c) provide such information and assistance as the Controller may reasonably request in relation to the Personal Data Breach; and

   (d) cooperate with the Controller in any investigation, including any investigation by a Supervisory Authority.

7.4 **Documentation**: The Processor shall maintain records of all Personal Data Breaches, including the facts relating to the breach, its effects, and the remedial action taken, and shall make such records available to the Controller and Supervisory Authorities upon request.

9.1 **Location of Processing**: The Processor shall process Personal Data in {{processing_location}}.

{{#if international_transfers}}
9.2 **Transfers Outside {{eea_or_uk_text}}**: Where Personal Data is transferred to, or processed in, a country outside the {{eea_or_uk_text}} that has not been recognised by the {{relevant_authority_text}} as providing adequate protection:

   (a) the parties shall enter into the Standard Contractual Clauses, which are hereby incorporated by reference and shall form part of this DPA;

   (b) for the purposes of the Standard Contractual Clauses:

      (i) the Controller is the "data exporter" and the Processor is the "data importer";

      (ii) the parties agree to comply with the relevant modules and clauses of the Standard Contractual Clauses as applicable to the relationship between controller and processor; and

      (iii) any terms not defined in this DPA shall have the meaning given in the Standard Contractual Clauses;

   (c) the Processor shall implement appropriate supplementary measures (technical, organisational, and contractual) to ensure that the level of protection guaranteed by the GDPR is not undermined, taking into account:

      (i) the circumstances of the transfer;

      (ii) the laws and practices of the destination country, including any government access to data; and

      (iii) the Security Measures applied;

   (d) the Processor shall provide the Controller with all information reasonably necessary to assess the adequacy of supplementary measures and compliance with Data Protection Legislation in relation to international transfers.

9.3 **UK Transfers**: Where Personal Data protected by the UK GDPR is transferred outside the UK:

   (a) the UK Addendum to the Standard Contractual Clauses (as approved by the UK Information Commissioner's Office) shall apply in addition to the Standard Contractual Clauses; and

   (b) the Processor shall comply with any additional requirements under UK Data Protection Legislation.
{{/if}}

{{^if international_transfers}}
9.2 **No International Transfers**: The Processor warrants that Personal Data shall not be transferred to, or processed in, any country outside the {{eea_or_uk_text}} without the Controller's prior written consent and without implementing appropriate safeguards as required by Data Protection Legislation.
{{/if}}

The Controller consents to the Processor engaging the following Sub-processors:

{{#if sub_processors_list}}
{{#sub_processors_list}}
### {{name}}

- **Service Provided**: {{service}}
- **Location**: {{location}}
- **Data Processed**: [Specify type of Personal Data processed by this Sub-processor]

{{/sub_processors_list}}
{{else}}
